### **2. Vercel AI Gateway Setup**

This is the first and most critical step.

1.  **Navigate to your Vercel Project Dashboard > AI Gateway.**
2.  **Create a New Gateway.**
3.  **Configure the Routes:** You will create four routes within this single gateway. A "route" maps a slug in the Gateway URL to a specific backend model provider.

| Route Slug (Example) | Model Provider | API Key (Stored in Vercel Env Vars) |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `grok-70b` | Grok | `GROK_API_KEY` |
| `claude-3-sonnet` | Anthropic | `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` |
| `gemini-1-5-pro` | Google (via Vertex AI or AI Studio) | `GOOGLE_API_KEY` |
| `judge-gemini-flash` | Google (via Vertex AI or AI Studio) | `GOOGLE_API_KEY` |

4.  **Environment Variables:** In your Vercel Project Settings, add the API keys for Grok, Anthropic, and Google. The AI Gateway will automatically and securely access these keys. You will also need to add your Gateway's URL to the environment variables.

    ```bash
    # .env.local (and in Vercel Project Settings)
    VERCEL_AI_GATEWAY_URL="https://gw.vercel.ai/..."
    ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="sk-ant-..."
    GROK_API_KEY="gsk_..."
    GOOGLE_API_KEY="AIzaSy..."
    ```

